As coronavirus continues to create fear and panic across the world, the minister of Health, Dr. Osagie Enahire, has said that people with underlying medical conditions and elderly people are more vulnerable. The minister, who stated this at a press conference on coronavirus update, yesterday in Abuja, explained that many people with the virus only have mild symptoms and recover quickly. He therefore advised senior citizens and people and people with underlying health conditions to stay at home most time. “It is important to note that many people who are infected with coronavirus will experience only mild symptoms and recover without incident. Of great concern are those with existing underlying medical conditions and senior citizens, who are known to be more vulnerable. We strongly advise these citizens to stay more at home.” The minister urged all Nigerians to maintain necessary precautions to protect themselves and their families, while identifying the measures as regularly hand wash with soap and water or use of an alcohol-based sanitiser if no water and soap is available. Speaking further on measures, Ehanire advised citizens to “maintain at least 2 metres distance between yourself and anyone who is coughing or sneezing. Persons with a persistent cough or sneezing, should stay at home and maintain a distance in gatherings. “Stay more at home and avoid congregating, especially if you feel unwell with symptoms like fever, cough and difficulty in breathing. “Stay informed on the latest developments about COVID-19 through the official Federal Ministry of Health, Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, Lagos State Ministry of Health and other State health department official channels on TV, radio and social media platforms.” 